dlew clean test -Pcoordinates=\\\"org.eclipse.jdt:ecj:3.32.0\\\"]\\n```\\n\\n\",\"comments\":[{\"id\":\"IC_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABBEFgBQ\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"MEMBER\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.eclipse.jdt:ecj:3.34.0`. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-5183-fails-native-image-run-org.eclipse.jdt-ecj-3.34.0-0ed92485\\n\\nRun metrics were unavailable, but the logs point to `run-consecutive-tests` timing out after Gradle had already reported success, not to a reproducible `ecj` metadata/native-image failure. `checkMetadataFiles` succeeded in all observed reruns (`logs/check-metadata-files/local-ci/gradlew-2026-05-03T13-54-39-794442Z.log`, `logs/check-metadata-files/local-ci/gradlew-2026-05-03T13-56-22-347106Z.log`, `logs/check-metadata-files/local-ci/gradlew-2026-05-03T13-58-00-730032Z.log`). In `logs/run-consecutive-tests/local-ci/bash-2026-05-03T13-38-18-694491Z.log`, the native-image test run reports 18/18 tests successful and `BUILD SUCCESSFUL`, then the wrapper is killed by the 5 minute timeout (`TIMEOUT: 'native-image run' ... exit code 137`); the follow-up `javac compile` bisect also shows `BUILD SUCCESSFUL` before another timeout. The same pattern appears in `logs/run-consecutive-tests/local-ci/bash-2026-05-03T13-58-25-302386Z.log` under `future-defaults-all`. For comparison, `logs/run-consecutive-tests/local-ci/bash-2026-05-03T13-54-43-671223Z.log` and `logs/run-consecutive-tests/local-ci/bash-2026-05-03T13-56-24-745122Z.log` both end with `PASSED:3.34.0`, which makes this look flaky and likely related to process shutdown/timeout handling rather than missing reachability metadata.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `logs/run-consecutive-tests/local-ci/bash-2026-05-03T13-38-18-694491Z.log`\\n- `logs/run-consecutive-tests/local-ci/bash-2026-05-03T13-58-25-302386Z.log`\\n- `logs/run-consecutive-tests/local-ci/bash-2026-05-03T13-54-43-671223Z.log`\\n- `logs/check-metadata-files/local-ci/gradlew-2026-05-03T13-58-00-730032Z.log`\\n- `logs/org.eclipse.jdt:ecj:3.34.0/local-ci-fixup/run-consecutive-tests-2026-05-03T13-48-58-850663Z.log`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Re-run `run-consecutive-tests.sh` for `org.eclipse.jdt:ecj:3.34.0` in both `current-defaults` and `future-defaults-all` modes and check whether any Gradle/Java process remains alive after `BUILD SUCCESSFUL`.\\n2. Compare the passing runs (`13-54-43`, `13-56-24`) against the timed-out runs (`13-38-18`, `13-58-25`) to isolate the shutdown difference.\\n3. If the timeout reproduces, capture thread/process state at the 5 minute mark and adjust the harness timeout/process handling instead of changing `ecj` reachability metadata.\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-03T14:11:05Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/5183#issuecomment-4366360581\",\"viewerDidAuthor\":true}],\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-03T12:13:02Z\",\"labels\":[{\"id\":\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAABz10A0g\",\"name\":\"library-unsupported-version\",\"description\":\"Automation found that the specific library version is not working with the current metadata.\",\"color\":\"bb366d\"},{\"id\":\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAACPb0ftA\",\"name\":\"fails-native-image-run\",\"description\":\"Tests fail in native execution\",\"color\":\"d93f0b\"},{\"id\":\"LA_kwDOHlghYc8AAAACe9gtkA\",\"name\":\"human-intervention\",\"description\":\"Requires manual follow-up because automated dynamic-access coverage remained too low\",\"color\":\"B60205\"}],\"number\":5183,\"title\":\"[Automation] native-image run fails for org.eclipse.jdt:ecj:3.34.0\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-03T14:11:11Z\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/5183\"}\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
